00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,118
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:45,150 --> 00:00:47,278
I want to understand irrational numbers.

3
00:00:49,613 --> 00:00:51,448
[Eui-ju] Understand? Me?

4
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:53,701
Why?

5
00:00:54,535 --> 00:00:55,536
Why?

6
00:00:55,619 --> 00:00:56,662
Why what?

7
00:00:56,745 --> 00:00:59,290
CHAPTER 29: SOMETIMES,
THE TRUTH CAN BE DANGEROUS

8
00:01:00,958 --> 00:01:02,751
Uh… Why…

9
00:01:04,378 --> 00:01:08,549
Why is it that
Pythagoras killed his student in the end?

10
00:01:11,844 --> 00:01:13,095
Don't you get it?

11
00:01:13,679 --> 00:01:17,600
Pythagoras couldn't stand the thought that
his world could collapse in a second.

12
00:01:19,977 --> 00:01:21,645
5TH CENTURY BC

13
00:01:21,729 --> 00:01:23,022
[playful music plays]

14
00:01:23,105 --> 00:01:24,398
[exhales sharply]

15
00:01:25,941 --> 00:01:28,027
-[gasps]
-What's the matter?

16
00:01:29,028 --> 00:01:30,029
[stutters] Master.

17
00:01:30,112 --> 00:01:31,322
PYTHAGOREAN MATH ACADEMY
CROTON, GREECE

18
00:01:31,405 --> 00:01:32,406
Have you…

19
00:01:32,489 --> 00:01:33,490
PYTHAGORAS, DIRECTOR

20
00:01:33,574 --> 00:01:35,200
…perhaps discovered something new?

21
00:01:36,243 --> 00:01:37,870
HIPPASUS, STUDENT

22
00:01:37,953 --> 00:01:39,663
I tried to express

23
00:01:40,456 --> 00:01:43,042
the length of the diagonal
of a unit square.

24
00:01:43,918 --> 00:01:46,545
And I tried to do it as a fraction.

25
00:01:46,629 --> 00:01:50,090
That's right. Every number can
be expressed as a ratio of integers.

26
00:01:50,174 --> 00:01:52,051
It's the absolute truth we teach.

27
00:01:52,134 --> 00:01:53,135
[Eui-ju] Well…

28
00:01:55,429 --> 00:01:57,389
It's just that, it doesn't work.

29
00:01:57,473 --> 00:01:59,141
-[sighs]
-What's that?

30
00:01:59,683 --> 00:02:00,768
The thing is

31
00:02:01,602 --> 00:02:03,854
this number cannot be expressed
as a fraction!

32
00:02:04,647 --> 00:02:05,689
Wait.

33
00:02:06,607 --> 00:02:09,360
Wait a minute. [breathing shakily]

34
00:02:11,445 --> 00:02:12,696
All right.

35
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:13,781
Prove it to me.

36
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,075
-[playful music plays]
-Okay.

37
00:02:16,992 --> 00:02:18,202
Okay.

38
00:02:20,829 --> 00:02:21,956
Got a square.

39
00:02:22,623 --> 00:02:23,624
Please watch.

40
00:02:30,214 --> 00:02:31,215
-[sighs]
-[buzzer sounds]

41
00:02:31,298 --> 00:02:32,758
I can't express it.

42
00:02:33,258 --> 00:02:34,510
-[sobbing] I just can't.
-[gasps]

43
00:02:39,014 --> 00:02:40,224
If you're right then,

44
00:02:40,891 --> 00:02:43,978
it means everything we've believed
up until now is just wrong.

45
00:02:47,856 --> 00:02:48,857
Have you…

46
00:02:50,776 --> 00:02:52,027
told anyone else about this?

47
00:02:53,153 --> 00:02:54,154
I haven't.

48
00:02:54,655 --> 00:02:56,490
I haven't told anyone else about it yet.

49
00:02:56,573 --> 00:02:58,242
I wanted to tell you first, master.

50
00:03:00,369 --> 00:03:01,662
[sighs] I see.

51
00:03:02,371 --> 00:03:03,414
That's a relief.

52
00:03:05,749 --> 00:03:07,209
Hippasus.

53
00:03:10,212 --> 00:03:11,213
Yes?

54
00:03:11,797 --> 00:03:13,048
Your proof

55
00:03:14,258 --> 00:03:16,802
-never existed in the first place.
-[dramatic music plays]

56
00:03:17,970 --> 00:03:20,180
[grunting] Master.

57
00:03:20,264 --> 00:03:24,101
The truth can be far too dangerous.

58
00:03:26,103 --> 00:03:27,271
[echoes] Master!

59
00:03:33,193 --> 00:03:34,403
[sighs]

60
00:03:34,486 --> 00:03:37,823
Irrational numbers meant the collapse
of his entire world.

61
00:03:40,534 --> 00:03:42,953
[Eui-ju sighs] He's such a math geek.

62
00:03:43,037 --> 00:03:46,165
His eyes light up
whenever he talks about math. It's freaky.

63
00:03:47,458 --> 00:03:48,459
Man.

64
00:03:51,128 --> 00:03:52,463
But then again…

65
00:03:53,881 --> 00:03:57,384
[sighs] …it's kind of cool.

66
00:04:04,725 --> 00:04:06,143
[yelps]

67
00:04:06,977 --> 00:04:07,978
Are you okay?

68
00:04:10,355 --> 00:04:13,484
[stutters] Y-Yes. I'm… I'm okay. [grunts]

69
00:04:14,318 --> 00:04:16,445
That's why you shouldn't space out
when you walk.

70
00:04:17,196 --> 00:04:18,197
Right.

71
00:04:18,864 --> 00:04:20,115
How embarrassing.

72
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:22,826
That doesn't count as embarrassing to you,
does it?

73
00:04:26,246 --> 00:04:30,250
They say doing something embarrassing
boosts your creativity.

74
00:04:30,334 --> 00:04:31,627
Ah.

75
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:34,922
So you're intentionally embarrassing
yourself? Is there anything more?

76
00:04:35,756 --> 00:04:38,092
It's not embarrassing
if I tell you in advance.

77
00:04:38,175 --> 00:04:40,219
I see. Go for the boost then.

78
00:04:40,844 --> 00:04:42,012
I'm rooting for you.

79
00:04:47,309 --> 00:04:48,310
EPISODE 9

80
00:04:48,393 --> 00:04:49,561
I'm home.

81
00:04:50,270 --> 00:04:52,397
[Ma] Oh! Go to the bathroom first.

82
00:04:52,481 --> 00:04:54,566
-[people talking on television]
-Huh? I'm okay.

83
00:04:55,275 --> 00:04:57,319
You can hardly do number two
when you're out.

84
00:04:57,402 --> 00:05:00,614
So the moment you come home, you have
to go straight to the bathroom, okay?

85
00:05:00,697 --> 00:05:03,534
And hey. [clicks tongue]
If you need to go, don't hold it.

86
00:05:03,617 --> 00:05:05,494
Just please make sure you go.

87
00:05:06,286 --> 00:05:08,247
[grunts] Okay!

88
00:05:08,330 --> 00:05:09,957
I can take care of it myself.

89
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,000
You don't have to tell me
even when I have to poop.

90
00:05:12,084 --> 00:05:14,795
It's because you can't take care of it
on your own! [clicks tongue]

91
00:05:16,547 --> 00:05:17,714
Okay!

92
00:05:18,549 --> 00:05:19,550
I'll go.

93
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:21,468
Geez.

94
00:05:21,552 --> 00:05:24,304
Maybe I should pay a personal visit
to your homeroom teacher.

95
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:26,348
[stutters] Why?

96
00:05:27,599 --> 00:05:30,144
He carried you all the way to the ER
on his back.

97
00:05:30,227 --> 00:05:32,688
That's something to be awfully sorry
and grateful for.

98
00:05:33,397 --> 00:05:35,065
Oh, no. There's no need to.

99
00:05:35,149 --> 00:05:36,316
I told him I was grateful.

100
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,360
And he's busy.
Don't ever reach out to him or anything.

101
00:05:38,443 --> 00:05:39,736
Don't do it ever, never!

102
00:05:40,404 --> 00:05:42,156
You're afraid of him, aren't you?

103
00:05:42,906 --> 00:05:45,325
Fair enough.
Judging by all the demerits you got,

104
00:05:45,826 --> 00:05:47,202
no wonder you're scared of him.

105
00:05:47,286 --> 00:05:49,580
[chuckles] Man,
that teacher must be brutal.

106
00:05:50,289 --> 00:05:52,040
You really got on his bad side.

107
00:05:52,624 --> 00:05:54,877
No, I mean… It's not that bad.

108
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:57,588
He's just a little…
a little blunt, I guess?

109
00:05:57,671 --> 00:06:00,132
He can be kind of prickly sometimes.

110
00:06:00,215 --> 00:06:03,552
But the truth is that
he's truly good at heart, you know?

111
00:06:03,635 --> 00:06:06,263
He's immature and childish at times.

112
00:06:06,346 --> 00:06:07,806
But he is truly good at heart.

113
00:06:08,432 --> 00:06:09,433
Heart.

114
00:06:10,309 --> 00:06:11,602
[playful music plays]

115
00:06:20,319 --> 00:06:21,486
[dog whines]

116
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:28,785
-[owl hooting]
-[exhales]

117
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,205
I get it.

118
00:06:31,288 --> 00:06:34,750
Smart people are known to be good
at manipulating others however they want.

119
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,002
That makes sense.

120
00:06:37,085 --> 00:06:39,296
I have been manipulated.

121
00:06:39,379 --> 00:06:41,340
I've been manipulated just like Mr. Yoon.

122
00:06:42,382 --> 00:06:44,134
After nagging and scolding you ten times,

123
00:06:44,218 --> 00:06:45,761
they say one nice thing,
and then you're like,

124
00:06:45,844 --> 00:06:48,222
"Oh? Maybe they're actually
a good person after all."

125
00:06:48,305 --> 00:06:50,682
Yeah, that's exactly how it works.
[chuckles]

126
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:56,438
Really. He's so mean to me all the time,

127
00:06:56,521 --> 00:06:58,273
but I suddenly have butterflies
in my stomach

128
00:06:58,357 --> 00:07:00,150
just because he said
he'd try to understand me?

129
00:07:00,234 --> 00:07:01,276
It's ridiculous!

130
00:07:01,777 --> 00:07:03,237
[sighs]

131
00:07:06,281 --> 00:07:08,533
You better snap out of it, Yeo Eui-ju.

132
00:07:08,617 --> 00:07:11,286
Don't even make eye contact
with Math from tomorrow on.

133
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:18,835
CHAPTER 30: SOMEONE
I SHOULDN'T AND CAN'T LIKE

134
00:07:22,547 --> 00:07:25,550
Hey, guys.
Did you read the article I sent?

135
00:07:25,634 --> 00:07:27,219
Professor Na Deul-i

136
00:07:27,844 --> 00:07:30,847
has been named the First-ever
Korean Recipient of the Fields Medal.

137
00:07:30,931 --> 00:07:32,015
What about it?

138
00:07:32,766 --> 00:07:34,101
Do you know her?

139
00:07:34,184 --> 00:07:35,519
No, I don't.

140
00:07:35,602 --> 00:07:36,895
But Woo-su does.

141
00:07:37,729 --> 00:07:38,981
Oh!

142
00:07:39,064 --> 00:07:40,941
She was his Olympiad mate
from middle school.

143
00:07:41,024 --> 00:07:42,067
Really?

144
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,151
[Dong-ju] Really?

145
00:07:43,235 --> 00:07:44,736
Aren't you jealous?

146
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:47,406
Don't you think that
it should've been you?

147
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,869
[sighs] If you hadn't given up
on that Olympiad.

148
00:07:54,121 --> 00:07:55,956
Actually, only if you had
gone and studied abroad…

149
00:07:56,039 --> 00:07:57,916
-[Gi-jeon clears throat]
-Stop it, Da-ju.

150
00:07:58,709 --> 00:08:00,127
Listen, I always knew he'd make it.

151
00:08:00,210 --> 00:08:03,046
I just never thought he'd be here
eating toast with me

152
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:04,840
and arguing with those math dropouts.

153
00:08:05,799 --> 00:08:08,010
-I'm talking about my friend, Ga Woo-su.
-[Gi-jeon sighs]

154
00:08:08,093 --> 00:08:10,053
Ga Woo-su, my genius friend!

155
00:08:12,306 --> 00:08:14,016
[sighs] Whatever.

156
00:08:14,641 --> 00:08:15,851
If he'd brought glory to Korea

157
00:08:15,934 --> 00:08:17,477
-by winning a Fields Medal--
-Stop.

158
00:08:17,561 --> 00:08:19,021
Shut it. [clicks tongue]

159
00:08:19,980 --> 00:08:21,940
So what if that professor won the medal?

160
00:08:25,152 --> 00:08:26,153
Hey.

161
00:08:26,695 --> 00:08:28,697
Do you even know what a Fields Medal is?

162
00:08:29,781 --> 00:08:31,033
I do. And?

163
00:08:31,116 --> 00:08:33,994
Then why don't you tell me who
the very first Fields Medal winner was.

164
00:08:38,790 --> 00:08:40,792
-David Copperfield.
-[sighs] I'm done.

165
00:08:40,876 --> 00:08:43,211
I refuse to waste my words on someone
who doesn't know that.

166
00:08:43,295 --> 00:08:44,421
[Gi-jeon scoffs]

167
00:08:44,504 --> 00:08:46,089
Anyway, Woo-su…

168
00:08:48,258 --> 00:08:49,801
[sighs] I'm done talking to you too.

169
00:08:50,427 --> 00:08:51,511
Enjoy your breakfast.

170
00:08:59,895 --> 00:09:01,813
I wonder when he'll head out.

171
00:09:01,897 --> 00:09:02,898
[giggles]

172
00:09:03,398 --> 00:09:05,150
He usually comes out around this time.

173
00:09:05,817 --> 00:09:08,820
Did I forget anything?
Did I forget all my textbooks?

174
00:09:08,904 --> 00:09:10,739
I should grab my puffer. [chuckles]

175
00:09:10,822 --> 00:09:13,492
Why isn't he coming out?
We're gonna be late. [chuckles]

176
00:09:13,575 --> 00:09:14,785
[Gi-jeon, Da-ju speaking]

177
00:09:14,868 --> 00:09:17,788
[Gi-jeon] Da-ju, hurry up!
It's been an hour since Woo-su left!

178
00:09:17,871 --> 00:09:19,956
-[Da-ju] He's driving me nuts.
-What the heck?

179
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,833
-[Eui-ju] What time is it?
-Hurry up. We're late.

180
00:09:22,334 --> 00:09:24,002
[groans] He's always like this.

181
00:09:25,045 --> 00:09:26,046
Isn't that Eui-ju?

182
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:28,423
It's Eui-ju.

183
00:09:28,507 --> 00:09:29,508
She's late too.

184
00:09:34,638 --> 00:09:37,182
[students] Good morning.

185
00:09:37,265 --> 00:09:38,642
Hello.

186
00:09:39,643 --> 00:09:42,437
[Eui-ju] Why does he
flip his hair like that?

187
00:09:42,521 --> 00:09:43,939
Let's get started right away.

188
00:09:45,315 --> 00:09:47,192
[Eui-ju] Why does he roll up his sleeve?

189
00:09:49,694 --> 00:09:51,321
Why are his fingers so long?

190
00:09:51,405 --> 00:09:52,531
[gentle music playing]

191
00:10:00,455 --> 00:10:01,873
[chuckles]

192
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:05,919
Why does he drink water like that?

193
00:10:09,172 --> 00:10:10,382
[sighs]

194
00:10:10,465 --> 00:10:12,008
He's spinning his pen.

195
00:10:14,428 --> 00:10:16,138
He's so… [inhales]

196
00:10:17,681 --> 00:10:18,682
He's so…

197
00:10:19,307 --> 00:10:20,350
so annoying.

198
00:10:22,269 --> 00:10:23,270
[grunts]

199
00:10:23,770 --> 00:10:25,897
What is it that you wanna tell me?

200
00:10:26,481 --> 00:10:27,691
Come and sit here first.

201
00:10:31,153 --> 00:10:32,154
[sighs]

202
00:10:32,904 --> 00:10:33,905
Go-ya.

203
00:10:33,989 --> 00:10:38,285
You know that fangirling used to be
my only joy in life.

204
00:10:38,952 --> 00:10:39,953
I know.

205
00:10:41,121 --> 00:10:44,916
Of course, I am aware that
they were all from a different world,

206
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,918
but my love for every one of them

207
00:10:47,002 --> 00:10:49,421
was always honest and real.

208
00:10:50,005 --> 00:10:51,965
Thinking about those characters

209
00:10:52,048 --> 00:10:53,884
gave me the strength to keep going.

210
00:10:54,968 --> 00:10:55,969
But now…

211
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,972
every time he crosses my mind…

212
00:11:00,932 --> 00:11:03,518
Oh, geez! I get so mad!

213
00:11:04,186 --> 00:11:05,187
[grunts]

214
00:11:05,687 --> 00:11:07,105
I really don't wanna think about him.

215
00:11:07,189 --> 00:11:09,483
I'm not supposed to think about him.

216
00:11:10,108 --> 00:11:11,443
But he's stuck in my head.

217
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,362
You're just in denial.

218
00:11:15,947 --> 00:11:16,948
In denial?

219
00:11:17,032 --> 00:11:18,533
You've always been like that.

220
00:11:18,617 --> 00:11:22,120
You watch idol videos all the time
but say you're not a fan.

221
00:11:22,662 --> 00:11:24,915
And you keep saving pictures
of that lead drama actor

222
00:11:24,998 --> 00:11:26,917
but claim
it's because he's good at acting.

223
00:11:28,126 --> 00:11:30,337
Do I do that?

224
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:32,047
Mmm… You do.

225
00:11:32,881 --> 00:11:35,926
You're already head over heels for him
but you're trying to deny it.

226
00:11:36,009 --> 00:11:38,637
Your words say otherwise, but
your heart is already racing toward him.

227
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,180
No, I can't.

228
00:11:41,473 --> 00:11:42,933
I can't.

229
00:11:43,517 --> 00:11:46,311
I can't! I shouldn't like him.
I simply can't!

230
00:11:46,978 --> 00:11:47,979
I just can't.

231
00:11:48,688 --> 00:11:50,857
Why? Huh?

232
00:11:52,484 --> 00:11:54,903
Why can't you like the PE teacher?

233
00:11:55,820 --> 00:11:56,821
[owl hooting]

234
00:11:59,407 --> 00:12:00,408
Huh?

235
00:12:01,576 --> 00:12:04,162
Why would you deny having a crush
on the PE teacher?

236
00:12:04,246 --> 00:12:05,455
[intriguing music plays]

237
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:07,040
Oh…

238
00:12:09,501 --> 00:12:10,877
No, that's not it.

239
00:12:10,961 --> 00:12:12,254
No.

240
00:12:13,088 --> 00:12:14,172
-Let's go?
-Huh?

241
00:12:14,256 --> 00:12:15,799
Never mind what I said. Come on.

242
00:12:15,882 --> 00:12:17,676
-Huh?
-Come on. Let's go.

243
00:12:19,219 --> 00:12:20,345
-Hey.
-Hi.

244
00:12:20,428 --> 00:12:21,555
Jenny, where are you going?

245
00:12:21,638 --> 00:12:22,889
Oh, teachers' office.

246
00:12:22,973 --> 00:12:25,892
I'm asking for permission
to go tour the city.

247
00:12:25,976 --> 00:12:27,727
Good for you. Where are you going?

248
00:12:27,811 --> 00:12:30,647
Oh. I'm going to go
to the Gyeongbokgung Palace in hanbok.

249
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,190
And then the market.

250
00:12:32,274 --> 00:12:34,234
I'm going
to have gimbap and tteokbokki there.

251
00:12:34,317 --> 00:12:37,404
Hongdae too. After Hongdae, I'm going
to the Han River to have ramyeon.

252
00:12:37,487 --> 00:12:38,905
And then N Seoul Tower too.

253
00:12:39,948 --> 00:12:41,241
Wow.

254
00:12:41,324 --> 00:12:44,828
You've got that much energy
to go to all those places?

255
00:12:44,911 --> 00:12:46,079
-Mm-hmm.
-Jenny,

256
00:12:46,162 --> 00:12:48,873
you know you have to write
a field trip report afterwards, right?

257
00:12:48,957 --> 00:12:50,917
Of course, I do.

258
00:12:51,001 --> 00:12:53,670
"I have learned a lot
about Korean culture."

259
00:12:53,753 --> 00:12:55,714
I just need to write it like that, right?

260
00:12:55,797 --> 00:12:56,798
[chuckles] Bye!

261
00:12:58,633 --> 00:13:01,886
She just… She has no idea
what the requirements are.

262
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:04,347
Let's just leave her be. She seems happy.

263
00:13:04,431 --> 00:13:05,849
[sighs] Oh, boy.

264
00:13:05,932 --> 00:13:07,809
THE DANCING CARNATION
NOTABLE WORK "MY MOTHER"

265
00:13:07,892 --> 00:13:08,893
BY YOON DONG-JU

266
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,284
Wow.

267
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:28,204
You're reading that book again?
You must know all the lines.

268
00:13:28,288 --> 00:13:29,289
[whispers] Yes, I do.

269
00:13:29,914 --> 00:13:34,919
"The face, which no longer smiled,
was embracing a flower in full bloom."

270
00:13:35,629 --> 00:13:39,883
If she no longer smiles, maybe
it means Dong-ju's mother passed away.

271
00:13:39,966 --> 00:13:42,594
When he writes,
"And a small flower with no answer,"

272
00:13:42,677 --> 00:13:45,847
it must mean that the small flower
is Dong-ju.

273
00:13:47,265 --> 00:13:49,976
But why didn't he answer
when his mother called for him?

274
00:13:50,477 --> 00:13:52,979
-Why didn't he look at her?
-[sighs]

275
00:13:53,063 --> 00:13:54,898
He probably resented his mother.

276
00:13:54,981 --> 00:13:58,526
[sobbing] I bet he probably regrets it
so much now.

277
00:14:00,153 --> 00:14:01,154
Man,

278
00:14:01,863 --> 00:14:05,533
you would've gotten a perfect score
on Korean lit if you studied like that.

279
00:14:07,118 --> 00:14:08,787
How is the poem coming along?

280
00:14:09,913 --> 00:14:10,914
Well…

281
00:14:14,334 --> 00:14:15,877
Hey. [mouthing]

282
00:14:19,381 --> 00:14:20,799
Hello.

283
00:14:25,303 --> 00:14:27,222
[gentle music plays]

284
00:14:42,028 --> 00:14:44,239
[somber music plays]

285
00:15:05,885 --> 00:15:06,886
Go-ya.

286
00:15:06,970 --> 00:15:08,763
Why didn't you come and talk to Mr. Yoon?

287
00:15:11,141 --> 00:15:12,976
You've gotten really close.

288
00:15:14,602 --> 00:15:15,603
What?

289
00:15:15,687 --> 00:15:18,398
No, he gave me some feedback
about my poem.

290
00:15:28,742 --> 00:15:30,702
I shouldn't like him, I simply can't.

291
00:15:31,369 --> 00:15:32,370
I just can't.

292
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:43,590
That's why you shouldn't space out
when you walk.

293
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:46,676
His voice,

294
00:15:47,427 --> 00:15:50,430
you could totally hear the concern
in his voice.

295
00:15:50,930 --> 00:15:51,973
[chuckles]

296
00:15:54,893 --> 00:15:56,728
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 6

297
00:15:59,814 --> 00:16:02,817
[Young-hee] You're supposed to be
running this company someday. But now?

298
00:16:03,318 --> 00:16:04,694
What is this I hear

299
00:16:05,779 --> 00:16:07,697
about you and some guy?

300
00:16:07,781 --> 00:16:09,616
Have you lost your mind?

301
00:16:09,699 --> 00:16:11,993
Who told you that? Tell me!

302
00:16:16,998 --> 00:16:18,249
I did. Ju Si-on.

303
00:16:20,043 --> 00:16:21,377
It was all for your sake.

304
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:23,379
It was you?

305
00:16:24,923 --> 00:16:25,965
Is this why you joined the company?

306
00:16:26,049 --> 00:16:28,802
To win my mother's favor
and just tell her about Yoon and me?

307
00:16:28,885 --> 00:16:29,969
[Da-ju scoffs]

308
00:16:30,053 --> 00:16:32,013
Honestly, I did it for your future.

309
00:16:33,515 --> 00:16:35,892
You're a man with a great future. [scoffs]

310
00:16:36,559 --> 00:16:39,479
You can't afford to be the subject
of any gossip.

311
00:16:39,562 --> 00:16:41,439
-Don't make me laugh.
-[chuckles]

312
00:16:41,523 --> 00:16:44,484
Yoon is never gonna choose you,
even if you tear us apart.

313
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:45,819
He was the first

314
00:16:46,945 --> 00:16:48,029
who laughed at my joke.

315
00:16:48,112 --> 00:16:49,322
There's no way.

316
00:16:50,073 --> 00:16:53,201
You see. Yoon laughed at all my jokes.

317
00:16:53,284 --> 00:16:55,203
He probably just did it
so you wouldn't feel embarrassed.

318
00:16:55,286 --> 00:16:57,330
Oh, no. Oh, no.

319
00:16:57,956 --> 00:16:58,957
You don't get it.

320
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:02,752
The way Yoon looks at me is completely
different from the way he looks

321
00:17:02,836 --> 00:17:04,170
at anyone else.

322
00:17:04,254 --> 00:17:05,630
-It's the same.
-No, it's not.

323
00:17:05,713 --> 00:17:07,257
-It's the same.
-No…

324
00:17:08,925 --> 00:17:11,010
You can take it out on me all you want.

325
00:17:11,094 --> 00:17:12,887
But if you mess with him, I won't have it.

326
00:17:12,971 --> 00:17:14,264
[scoffs]

327
00:17:17,141 --> 00:17:19,727
-No, you're not going anywhere.
-Move.

328
00:17:19,811 --> 00:17:22,188
No way. I'll never let you… [shrieks]

329
00:17:22,272 --> 00:17:25,024
-Mr. Kim!
-[Kim] Yes, Madam Chairman!

330
00:17:28,278 --> 00:17:32,574
Tie him up and don't let him go until you
handle Choi Yoon or whatever his name is.

331
00:17:35,994 --> 00:17:38,121
-Get off me. Get off!
-[groans]

332
00:17:40,248 --> 00:17:41,499
[groans]

333
00:17:43,293 --> 00:17:44,294
[shouts]

334
00:17:45,336 --> 00:17:46,337
[Young-hee] Get him!

335
00:17:49,716 --> 00:17:52,010
[tires squealing]

336
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,183
[grunting]

337
00:18:08,735 --> 00:18:10,236
[laughing]

338
00:18:46,356 --> 00:18:47,398
[panting]

339
00:18:51,569 --> 00:18:52,570
Are you okay?

340
00:18:53,154 --> 00:18:55,490
This is why I told you never to be alone,
Choi Yoon!

341
00:18:56,908 --> 00:18:57,951
Are you not hurt?

342
00:19:06,626 --> 00:19:07,627
Let's go.

343
00:19:15,551 --> 00:19:17,095
[gasps]

344
00:19:19,597 --> 00:19:21,599
Oh! What am I doing?

345
00:19:23,142 --> 00:19:25,812
[breathes shakily] Why…
Why did I turn into Yoon?

346
00:19:25,895 --> 00:19:27,188
Why did I turn into Mr. Yoon?

347
00:19:28,648 --> 00:19:30,525
It's so smooth. Why is it so vivid?

348
00:19:32,318 --> 00:19:33,444
Could this be…

349
00:19:35,113 --> 00:19:36,447
[playful music plays]

350
00:19:36,531 --> 00:19:37,573
Oh.

351
00:19:41,119 --> 00:19:44,414
TOPOLOGY OF ALGEBRAIC CURVES
AND SURFACES

352
00:19:50,169 --> 00:19:51,754
HEY, IT'S BEEN A WHILE

353
00:19:51,838 --> 00:19:53,840
I'M BACK IN KOREA
CAN WE MEET UP?

354
00:19:59,053 --> 00:20:00,555
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

355
00:20:06,894 --> 00:20:08,855
[pensive music plays]

356
00:20:08,938 --> 00:20:10,064
[no audible dialogue]

357
00:20:17,655 --> 00:20:18,656
Okay.

358
00:20:24,412 --> 00:20:25,788
Huh? Go-ya.

359
00:20:29,876 --> 00:20:31,169
I need to talk to you.

360
00:20:38,801 --> 00:20:40,344
What was that just now?

361
00:20:40,428 --> 00:20:44,474
Oh. You mean that I told him I was
having trouble coming up with a title

362
00:20:44,557 --> 00:20:45,558
for the poem.

363
00:20:45,641 --> 00:20:48,895
So he said that I should try using
the first image that comes to mind

364
00:20:48,978 --> 00:20:51,314
or a word that shows up a lot in the poem.

365
00:20:51,397 --> 00:20:54,567
So I just asked him
to please check a few options for me.

366
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:56,152
And why did you go alone?

367
00:20:56,235 --> 00:20:57,361
You could've invited me.

368
00:20:58,529 --> 00:21:03,242
Well, I was going to. But I decided to go
alone because it wasn't a big deal.

369
00:21:03,868 --> 00:21:05,203
"Not a big deal"?

370
00:21:06,454 --> 00:21:09,874
I'm always too nervous to even
bring myself to say hello to Dong-ju.

371
00:21:09,957 --> 00:21:13,252
But laughing and talking with him
is not a big deal to you?

372
00:21:13,878 --> 00:21:15,088
[wistful music plays]

373
00:21:17,298 --> 00:21:18,883
Oh, that's…

374
00:21:18,966 --> 00:21:20,051
Be honest with me.

375
00:21:20,927 --> 00:21:22,470
Mr. Jung's not your crush is he?

376
00:21:23,304 --> 00:21:24,555
You have a crush on Dong-ju.

377
00:21:26,265 --> 00:21:27,266
What are you talking about?

378
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:28,643
I know you do.

379
00:21:28,726 --> 00:21:30,686
Otherwise, why would you go alone
to talk to him?

380
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,480
Why would you be in denial?

381
00:21:34,941 --> 00:21:36,734
[sighs] No.

382
00:21:36,818 --> 00:21:38,861
I wasn't talking about Mr. Yoon.

383
00:21:42,615 --> 00:21:44,367
[sighs] Ah…

384
00:21:44,450 --> 00:21:47,745
Why can't you just…
just say something to me then?

385
00:21:47,829 --> 00:21:50,456
Anyone can see
you're acting suspicious right now.

386
00:21:52,542 --> 00:21:53,543
[sighs]

387
00:21:54,168 --> 00:21:55,211
Can't you trust me?

388
00:21:57,171 --> 00:21:59,674
-What?
-Why can't you believe me.

389
00:21:59,757 --> 00:22:01,134
I already said no.

390
00:22:01,676 --> 00:22:03,761
Have I ever lied to you
about anything before?

391
00:22:05,304 --> 00:22:06,389
[sighs]

392
00:22:07,431 --> 00:22:08,432
Fine.

393
00:22:09,183 --> 00:22:10,184
Let's go with that.

394
00:22:10,268 --> 00:22:13,729
I'm just so blinded by a man that
I can't trust my innocent friend.

395
00:22:17,525 --> 00:22:18,693
[sighs]

396
00:22:22,738 --> 00:22:25,116
-It wouldn't be me, right? It wasn't…
-It was me. I did it.

397
00:22:25,199 --> 00:22:26,200
Did you get choco balls?

398
00:22:26,284 --> 00:22:27,326
Whatever.

399
00:22:36,043 --> 00:22:37,044
Hey.

400
00:22:37,670 --> 00:22:38,671
What's wrong with her?

401
00:22:43,259 --> 00:22:45,678
-You think they had a fight?
-They definitely had a fight.

402
00:22:45,761 --> 00:22:46,846
I think so.

403
00:22:46,929 --> 00:22:48,347
-[Dan-ji] Geez.
-It's so weird.

404
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,642
[sighs]

405
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:57,481
[grunts]

406
00:22:58,399 --> 00:23:00,234
[sighs]

407
00:23:02,069 --> 00:23:03,362
[somber music plays]

408
00:23:08,451 --> 00:23:10,953
I hope she won't be angry too long.

409
00:23:13,831 --> 00:23:14,832
[sighs]

410
00:23:28,221 --> 00:23:33,309
CHAPTER 31:
EVERYONE HAS A SPECIAL SOMEONE

411
00:23:45,571 --> 00:23:46,572
[sniffs]

412
00:23:48,574 --> 00:23:49,659
Oh.

413
00:23:50,284 --> 00:23:51,285
What the heck?

414
00:23:52,828 --> 00:23:56,457
Why am I waiting for Math
when Mr. Jung walked out of his house?

415
00:23:57,375 --> 00:23:58,376
[gasps]

416
00:23:58,876 --> 00:24:00,211
Oh, no.

417
00:24:00,294 --> 00:24:03,130
When I look at his face, it feels…

418
00:24:03,214 --> 00:24:04,674
Are you okay?

419
00:24:05,716 --> 00:24:06,759
[gasps]

420
00:24:07,426 --> 00:24:08,511
[grunts]

421
00:24:09,136 --> 00:24:10,137
No way.

422
00:24:27,905 --> 00:24:29,991
[Go-ya] Love is like first snow.

423
00:24:30,491 --> 00:24:31,617
Right in that moment.

424
00:24:32,118 --> 00:24:33,286
When you see them…

425
00:24:33,786 --> 00:24:36,622
Oh! And you know they're the one.

426
00:24:37,164 --> 00:24:39,166
It always comes when you least expect it.

427
00:24:42,295 --> 00:24:43,671
MINI MOCK EXAMINATION 7

428
00:24:48,050 --> 00:24:50,052
[Eui-Ju] My first love.

429
00:24:50,636 --> 00:24:52,888
My first love is Math and not PE?

430
00:24:55,266 --> 00:24:56,350
What do I do?

431
00:24:58,060 --> 00:25:01,063
What do I do? What do I do?

432
00:25:06,986 --> 00:25:08,070
[phone buzzes]

433
00:25:08,154 --> 00:25:09,613
[barista] Your large mocha's ready.

434
00:25:11,699 --> 00:25:13,284
Thank you. Enjoy your coffee.

435
00:25:13,367 --> 00:25:14,994
Thank you very much.

436
00:25:15,077 --> 00:25:16,203
[sighs]

437
00:25:26,964 --> 00:25:27,965
Oh.

438
00:25:32,636 --> 00:25:33,637
[chuckles]

439
00:25:34,138 --> 00:25:35,139
What the heck?

440
00:25:35,973 --> 00:25:37,308
What is he doing here?

441
00:25:38,642 --> 00:25:39,810
[gasps]

442
00:25:39,894 --> 00:25:41,145
Why didn't I see him earlier?

443
00:25:41,228 --> 00:25:42,229
Hold on.

444
00:25:42,313 --> 00:25:45,733
When I ordered this,
I was up at the counter.

445
00:25:46,484 --> 00:25:48,444
[chuckles] Oh man. [laughs]

446
00:25:49,153 --> 00:25:51,322
Wait. Uh… Hold on.

447
00:25:51,405 --> 00:25:53,532
Did he know I was here,
that I like this place?

448
00:25:53,616 --> 00:25:54,867
Oh, my…

449
00:25:54,950 --> 00:25:56,327
[clears throat] Maybe not.

450
00:25:57,578 --> 00:26:00,164
Is this what people call destiny?
[chuckles]

451
00:26:03,209 --> 00:26:04,210
What's that?

452
00:26:06,712 --> 00:26:07,838
Is that a mocha?

453
00:26:11,175 --> 00:26:12,176
[gasps]

454
00:26:12,259 --> 00:26:15,054
-[Woo-su chuckles]
-[chuckles] It's so not like him.

455
00:26:15,805 --> 00:26:18,224
And he added so much whipped cream on top.

456
00:26:18,307 --> 00:26:21,227
Oh, please. It looks just like mine.

457
00:26:21,894 --> 00:26:22,895
What's with him?

458
00:26:26,607 --> 00:26:29,110
Huh? Why is he waving his hand?

459
00:26:29,193 --> 00:26:30,694
[door opens]

460
00:26:33,531 --> 00:26:34,949
[person chuckles]

461
00:26:35,032 --> 00:26:36,117
[wistful music plays]

462
00:26:38,994 --> 00:26:40,121
Been a while.

463
00:26:40,204 --> 00:26:42,665
-I've missed you so much.
-[both chuckle]

464
00:26:45,292 --> 00:26:48,170
[Eui-ju] I really didn't know
what to make of my feelings.

465
00:26:48,921 --> 00:26:49,922
But then

466
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,550
it all became very clear.

467
00:26:56,137 --> 00:27:01,183
What those reckless, aimless feelings
of mine had really been all along.

468
00:27:03,477 --> 00:27:04,895
Everyone has someone like that,

469
00:27:06,397 --> 00:27:07,481
at least once,

470
00:27:08,482 --> 00:27:11,652
someone who can make
your heart suddenly drop.

